{
  "texts": [
    "Manocchio et al., through their proposed FlowTransformer framework [10], have shown that transformer architectures perform well on binary Net-Flow classification tasks when trained on complete datasets.",
    "This performance is achieved without the need pre-training on natural language datasets.",
    "For instance, their model, using GPT's architecture achieves an 89.98% F1-score.",
    "ExplainabilityThe analysis of LLama3 generated explanations for various prediction cases reveal unique benefits and notable limitations to enrich future NIDS applications with explainability, a unique feature proper to LLMs.",
    "These sample prompts demonstrate that LLMs can provide detailed and contextually relevant explanations for their classifications of network flows but with notable limitations."
  ]
}